               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301028-140-person1201">
                  JOHN 
                  INGARFIELD
               <interp inst="t18301028-140-person1201" type="surname" value="INGARFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301028-140-person1201" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301028-140-person1201" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live opposite Mr. Purssord. On the 18th of October I saw the prisoner lurking about his shop - Mr. Purssord was talking to me; I turned my back, went into my parlour, and took a glass of ale - I then missed the prisoner from the prosecutor's window, and I saw Mr. Purssord's boy standing in the street; he seemed confused - I ran down a street towards Red Lion-square; I there found the prisoner, and took him back - he struck me a violent blow, and said it was put there for a trap.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301028-140-person1202">
                  GEORGE 
                  SMITH
